meanings.definition: (Greek mythology) A son of Aegyptus, slain by his wife Danais.
meanings.english_definition: In Greek mythology, Phyteus was one of the sons of Aegyptus, killed by his wife Danais on their wedding night.

etymology.value: From Ancient Greek Φυτεύς (Phyteús), possibly related to φυτεύω (phyteúō, "to plant").
